dependence on the impurity charge. Transport outside r/a = 0.3 is well 
described by the nonlinear turbulent calculations but the central region is 
predicted to be below the turbulence threshold while the observed transport is 
one order of magnitude higher than neoclassical values. The gyrokinetic 
calculations evidence the dominant role of the curvature pinch in the total 
convective flux. This term is directed inwards and only weakly dependent on the 
impurity charge in the explored range of species.},
